title_orig_left: Stethoscope - A device used for listening to internal sounds in the body, commonly used for listening to heart and lung sounds.
Thermometer - An instrument used to measure body temperature.
Sphygmomanometer - A device used to measure blood pressure.
Otoscope - A tool used for visual examination of the ear canal and eardrum.
Ophthalmoscope - An instrument for inspecting the retina and other parts of the eye.
ECG (Electrocardiogram) Machine - Used to record the electrical activity of the heart over a period of time.
Ultrasound Machine - Utilizes high-frequency sound waves to create images of the inside of the body.
X-ray Machine - Used for radiography to view the internal structure of an object.
MRI Scanner - Employs magnetic fields and radio waves to create detailed images of the organs and tissues.
CT Scanner - Uses X-rays and computer technology to create cross-sectional images of the body.
Spirometer - Measures the air capacity of the lungs.
Glucometer - A device for measuring the level of glucose in the blood.
Pulse Oximeter - Used to measure the oxygen saturation of the blood.
Laryngoscope - An instrument used to examine the larynx.
Blood Pressure Monitor - A device to measure blood pressure.
Endoscope - A flexible tube with a light and camera attached to it, used to look inside the body.
Defibrillator - A device that delivers a dose of electric current to the heart to treat life-threatening cardiac dysrhythmias.
Pacemaker - A medical device that uses electrical impulses to regulate the beating of the heart.
Audiometer - Used to evaluate hearing acuity.
Tonometer - Measures the pressure inside the eye, used for glaucoma testing.
Electroencephalogram (EEG) Machine - Used to record the electrical activity of the brain.
Nebulizer - Converts liquid medication into a mist to be inhaled into the lungs.
Hemoglobinometer - Measures the concentration of hemoglobin in blood.
Biopsy Needle - A needle used to take a small piece of tissue for examination.
Fundus Camera - Used for photographing the interior surface of the eye, including the retina.
Doppler Ultrasound - Uses sound waves to measure the flow of blood through blood vessels.
Bone Densitometer - Measures bone mineral density for osteoporosis diagnosis.
Colposcope - A microscope used to examine the cervix, vagina, and vulva.
PET Scanner (Positron Emission Tomography) - Creates images of the body by detecting radiation emitted from a radioactive substance.
Laparoscope - A small tube with a light and camera used for examining the abdominal cavity.
Retinoscope - Used to determine the refractive error of the eye and the required prescription for glasses.
Arthroscope - A type of endoscope inserted into joint spaces for diagnosis and treatment.
Microscope - An instrument used to see objects that are too small for the naked eye.
Centrifuge - A machine that uses centrifugal force to separate substances of different densities.
Flow Cytometer - Used for analyzing the physical and chemical characteristics of particles in a fluid.
Scalpel - A small and extremely sharp bladed instrument used for surgery.
Forceps - A handheld, hinged instrument used for grasping and holding objects.
Surgical Scissors - Used for cutting tissues during surgery.
Needle Holder - A surgical instrument used to hold a suturing needle for closing wounds.
Suture Material - Used for stitching wounds together.
Hemostat - A surgical tool used to control bleeding.
Retractor - A surgical instrument used to separate the edges of a surgical incision or wound.
Surgical Gown - A personal protective garment worn by health care personnel during surgical procedures.
Surgical Gloves - Used to maintain a sterile environment during surgical procedures.
Surgical Mask - Worn by healthcare professionals to prevent contamination.
Surgical Cap - Worn to keep the surgical area free from contamination.
Surgical Drapes - Used to provide a sterile field during surgical procedures.
Surgical Swabs - Used to absorb blood and other fluids during surgery.
Surgical Stapler - A device used to close skin wounds, connect or remove parts of the bowels or lungs.
Electrosurgical Unit - Used for cutting and coagulating during surgical procedures.
Claritin is a non-drowsy antihistamine used to relieve symptoms of allergy, such as runny nose, sneezing, and itchy eyes.
Zyrtec effectively treats allergic symptoms such as itching, runny nose, and watery eyes, and is known for its fast action.
Allegra provides relief from seasonal allergy symptoms including sneezing, runny nose, itchy eyes, and hives.
Benadryl is an antihistamine that can treat allergy symptoms such as hives, itching, and swelling, but may cause drowsiness.
Nasacort is a nasal spray used to treat allergy symptoms like nasal congestion, sneezing, and itchy nose.
NyQuil is a nighttime cold and flu medicine that relieves symptoms such as sore throat, fever, and congestion.
Sudafed is a decongestant that relieves sinus pressure and nasal congestion associated with colds and allergies.
Tylenol Cold & Flu offers relief from cold and flu symptoms, including fever, headache, and cough.
Mucinex is an expectorant that helps reduce chest congestion caused by colds, infections, or allergies.
Alka-Seltzer Plus Cold provides relief from cold symptoms like nasal congestion, cough, and body aches.
Robitussin is a cough suppressant that relieves cough caused by minor throat and bronchial irritation.

title_orig_left: Vicks VapoRub is a topical cough suppressant with medicated vapors that help relieve cough and nasal congestion.
Delsym is a long-acting cough suppressant that provides relief from cough for up to 12 hours.
Cough DM is an over-the-counter medication used to temporarily relieve cough caused by the common cold or inhaled irritants.
Theraflu is a combination medicine used to treat headache, fever, body aches, cough, and congestion caused by the flu or common cold.
